'''Nazanin Boniadi''' (born May 22, 1980 in [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]) is a [[British Iranians|British Iranian]] actress<ref>http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2258164/</ref> currently living and working in the [[US]]. She got her first big break on the ABC soap opera, [[General Hospital]] and its SOAPnet spin-off series, [[General Hospital: Night Shift]] as [[Leyla Mir|Nurse Leyla Mir]]. She has mostly starred in TV with a few movies to her credit also, including the recent blockbuster ''"Iron Man"''.

She was nominated for an [[NAACP Image Award]] for ''"Outstanding Actress in a Daytime Drama Series"'' in 2008 for her role in General Hospital.<ref>http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2258164/</ref> She was also the cover girl for the Iranian-American lifestyle [[OCPC Magazine]] in 2006 in which she gave an interview on her career and the future.

==Filmography==
*[[Shades of Ray]] (2008) (completed) as ''"Farah"'' 
*General Hospital (2007-2008) as ''"Leyla Mir"''
*[[Iron Man (film)|Iron Man]] (2008) as ''"FBX Reporter"''  
*General Hospital: Night Shift as ''"Leyla Mir"''
*[[The Game]] (2007) as ''"Josie"''
*[[Gameface]] (2007) as ''"Taylor"''
*[[Kal: Yesterday & Tomorrow]] (2006) as ''"Simmi"''

